&lt;p data-start=&quot;87&quot; data-end=&quot;172&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Plumbing Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cool Willy’s – Tucson, AZ&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation: $80,000–$110,000 per year, depending on experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full-Time Leadership Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cool Willy’s is looking for a strong, organized, and results-driven &lt;strong&gt;Plumbing Manager&lt;/strong&gt; to lead and develop our growing plumbing department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not a position where you need to be the most technically experienced plumber in the building.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We already have strong sales talent and experienced field supervision in place. What we need is a leader who can bring the entire department together by creating structure, developing employees, implementing processes, improving communication, driving accountability, and helping the team consistently execute at a high level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Knowledge of the plumbing industry is strongly preferred, and hands-on plumbing experience is a plus. However, we are most interested in finding an experienced leader who understands how to organize and grow a service department, develop people, improve processes, and drive business performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lead the day-to-day operations of the residential plumbing department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Create structure, organization, and clear expectations across the department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Develop, coach, and mentor plumbing team members to improve performance and support career growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Establish consistent processes and ensure the team follows company procedures and operational standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Create clear accountability around individual and departmental performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Conduct regular one-on-one meetings, performance reviews, coaching sessions, and team meetings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Partner closely with field supervisors and sales leaders to improve communication and execution across the department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Monitor key performance indicators, including revenue, conversion rates, average ticket, callbacks, productivity, customer satisfaction, and other operational metrics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Use performance data to identify problems, develop action plans, and improve departmental results.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Help technicians improve their communication, customer service, and ability to confidently present solutions to homeowners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Identify training and development opportunities for team members.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assist with recruiting, interviewing, hiring, onboarding, and retaining high-performing employees.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Improve communication and collaboration between technicians, dispatch, customer service, sales, and company leadership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Help implement and maintain efficient scheduling, staffing, and workforce planning processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Address performance issues quickly and consistently while creating a culture of accountability and continuous improvement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support the continued growth, profitability, and scalability of the plumbing department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Proven experience

