&lt;p data-start=&quot;931&quot; data-end=&quot;1037&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;934&quot; data-end=&quot;954&q

&lt;div class=&quot;jd-section-employer&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;jd-description-text&quot;&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&quot;css-rktbgm e1tiznh50&quot;&gt;Senior Accountant&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&amp;nbsp;1435 S Euclid Ave, Tucson, AZ 85713 | In-Office Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: $75,000 per year&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full-Time | Full Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cool Willy’s is looking for an experienced &lt;strong&gt;Senior Accountant&lt;/strong&gt; to join our growing team in Tucson, Arizona. This is a full-time, in-office position for an accounting professional who has a strong understanding of full-cycle accounting and enjoys taking ownership of financial processes, solving problems, and ensuring accurate and timely financial reporting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will have an accounting degree, hands-on full-cycle accounting experience, and the ability to work independently while partnering with operational leaders and the broader finance team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Manage and perform full-cycle accounting activities, including accounts payable, accounts receivable, general ledger maintenance, journal entries, accruals, and account reconciliations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assist with and take ownership of month-end and year-end close processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Prepare accurate and timely financial reports and supporting schedules.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Perform bank, credit card, balance sheet, and general ledger reconciliations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Review financial activity, identify discrepancies and variances, and research and resolve accounting issues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maintain accurate general ledger accounts and ensure transactions are recorded in the appropriate accounting periods and accounts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assist with cash management, expense tracking, and financial reporting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support budgeting, forecasting, and financial analysis as needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maintain accurate documentation and internal controls to support financial reporting and audit requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Partner with operational leaders and other departments to improve accounting processes and ensure accurate financial information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assist with audits, tax preparation, and other accounting projects as needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Identify opportunities to improve accounting processes, reporting accuracy, and overall efficiency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Accounting required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong full-cycle accounting experience required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience in a Senior Accountant or similar accounting position preferred.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong understanding of GAAP and general accounting principles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience with month-end close, journal entries, account reconciliations, and financial reporting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong Excel skills and experience working with accounting software.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent analytical and problem-solving abilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong attention to detail and commitment to accuracy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to manage multiple priorities and meet deadlines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong communication skills and the ability to work effectively with accounting, finance, and operational teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
